Good evening, and welcome to our daily roundup of the latest developments on the coronavirus pandemic in Australia.
He revealed data that Australians were travelling 13% less this year compared to last year’s Easter holiday.
“We said before this weekend that Easter could be the most important weekend in our fight against the coronavirus,” he said.
Tasmanian health authorities also said at least 300 people had already had close contacts with confirmed coronavirus cases in the northwest.
Nationally, Australia now has 6,335 people diagnosed with Covid-19, 81 in intensive care and 35 on ventilators.